DefaultReaderConfiguration.description: Cisco (NAC) Network Access Control Appliance with Clean Access Manager (CAM) or Server (CAS) Software
DefaultReaderConfiguration.fullDescription: Collects events from Cisco NAC (clean access) appliances.

file.toolTipText: Directory or path to read from

string.toolTipText: Hostname of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

integer.toolTipText: Port number of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

select.toolTipText: Data routing (normalized alerts to Manager and/or raw data to nDepth)

integer.toolTipText: Number of seconds between log reads

FastToolId.description: Cisco (NAC) Network Access Control Appliance with Clean Access Manager (CAM) or Server (CAS) Software

FastPattern.description: 1, PolicyAccess: Administration:(MAC (added to|update to the|removed from the) list) / (API getlocaluserlist): Succeeded!
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*((API getlocaluserlist): Succeeded!)?([A-F\d:]{17} (added to|update to the|removed from the) (certified device|(Floating )?MAC) list)?

FastPattern.description: 2, PolicyAccess: Administration:IP updated in Clean Access Manager
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*[.\d]+ updated in Clean Access Manager

FastPattern.description: 3, PolicyAccess: Administration:\s*IP/Port updated in the SUBNET list
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*[.\d]+/\d+ updated in the SUBNET list

FastPattern.description: 4, PolicyAccess: Administration:IP/IP added to Route list
5, PolicyAccess: Administration:Application added to the Software Checklist
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*.+ added to the Software Checklist

FastPattern.description: 6, PolicyAccess: Administration:Updated policy to IP
7, PolicyAccess: Administration: Updated MacMappingInfo for SSID
8, PolicyAccess: Administration:Application List modified. All other (checks|rules) are unchanged
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*.+ modified\. All other (?:checks|rules) are unchanged

FastField.defaultValue: Application List modified. All other checks are unchanged

FastPattern.description: 9, UserLogon: Administration:Admin user session is created, login succeeded
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(Administration):\s*Admin user session is created, login succeeded\. Name:([^,]+), Group:([^,]+), IP:([^,]+), .+
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*Admin user session is created, login succeeded

FastPattern.description: 10, UserLogoff: Administration:Admin user session expired, automatically logged out
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(Administration):\s*Admin user session expired, automatically logged out\. Name:([^,]+), Group:([^,]+), IP:([^,]+), .+
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*Admin user session expired, automatically logged out

FastPattern.description: 11, UserLogoff: Administration:forcefully logged out by Administrator

FastField.defaultValue: Reason: forcefully logged out by Administrator, SourceMac: "$4"

FastPattern.description: 12, UserLogoff: Administration:forcefully logged out by Administrator (Multiple Logoffs)

FastField.defaultValue: Reason: forcefully logged out by Administrator, $4

FastPattern.description: 13, ServiceInfo: Administration:role is created successfully
14, ServiceWarning: Administration:Request is missing some security credential
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*Request is missing some security credential

FastPattern.description: 15, UserLogoff: Authentication: Session Timeout
16, UserLogoff: Authentication: going to logout user
17, UserLogonFailure: Authentication: Unable to login|Invalid username or password|Unknown user
FastPattern.pattern: Authentication:\s*(Unable to login|Invalid username or password|Unknown user)

FastPattern.description: 18, UserLogoff: Authentication: [Ll]ogged out
19, UserLogon: Authentication: Successfully logged in as out-of-band user
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(Authentication):\s*\[([A-F\d:]{17}) ## ([.\d]+)\] (.+?) - Successfully logged in as (.*) user, Provider: ([^,]+), Role: ([^,]+), OS: .*

FastPattern.description: 20, UserLogon: Authentication: Successfully logged in
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(Authentication):\s*\[([A-F\d:]{17}) ## ([.\d]+)\] (.+?) - Successfully logged in[^,]*, Provider: ([^,]+), L2 MAC address: ([A-F\d:]{17})(?:, Role: ([^,]+), OS: )?.*

FastPattern.description: 21, UserAuthAudit: Authentication: Windows TCP/IP stack detected
FastPattern.pattern: Authentication:.*Windows TCP/IP stack detected. User OS will be detected as

FastPattern.description: 22, UserAuthAudit: Authentication: Already logged in
23, UserAuthAudit: Authentication: Too many users using this account
FastPattern.pattern: Authentication:\s*Too many users using this account

FastPattern.description: 24, UserAuthAudit: Authentication: has successfully removed his oldest session
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(Authentication):\s*([^[]+) has successfully removed his oldest session:\s*\[([A-F\d:]{17}) ## ([.\d]+)\] (\S+)
FastPattern.pattern: Authentication:.*has successfully removed his oldest session:

FastField.defaultValue: "$7" has successfully removed his oldest session

FastPattern.description: 25, SoftwareInstall: CleanAccess:Automatic update is successful - already installed
FastPattern.pattern: CleanAccess:\s*Automatic .* update scheduled at [\d :/]+ is successful.*already installed

FastPattern.description: 26, SoftwareUpdate: CleanAccess:Automatic update is successful
FastPattern.pattern: CleanAccess:\s*Automatic .* update scheduled at [\d :/]+ is successful

FastPattern.description: 27, ServiceInfo: CleanAccess:Start the timer of certified device list
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(CleanAccess):\s*Start the timer of certified device list \[([^]]+)\]\. ([^[]+)\[([^]]+)\] (.*)
FastPattern.pattern: CleanAccess:\s*Start the timer of certified device list

FastField.defaultValue: Start the timer of certified device list "$4"

FastPattern.description: 28, ServiceInfo: CleanAccess:Timer of certified device list
29, SystemStatus: CleanAccessServer: System Stats:
NullAlert: CleanAccessServer: System Stats: BLANK
30, SystemStatus: CleanAccessServer: NAC Server info
31, UserLogoff: Client: Logout request
32, SystemStatus: Miscellaneous:Overwrote logs to keep the event log limit
FastPattern.pattern: Miscellaneous:\s*Overwrote \d+ logs .+ to keep the event log limit\.

FastPattern.description: 33, SystemStatus: Miscellaneous: successfully published registration page
34, UserLogonFailure: SW_Management:Unable to process login request from
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(SW_Management):\s*Unable to process ?(.*) login request from \[([A-F\d:]{17}) ## ([.\d]+)\] (\S+)\. Cause: (.+)\.
FastPattern.pattern: SW_Management:\s*Unable to process.* login request from

FastPattern.description: 35, UserLogoff: SW_Management:Successfully remove Out-of-Band user
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(SW_Management):\s*Received Link-Down trap from switch \[?([.\d]+)\]? port \[?(\d+)\]?\. Successfully remove Out-of-Band user \[OOB ## ([A-F\d:]{17}) ## ([.\d]+)\] (.+)\.

FastField.defaultValue: $6, Received Link-Down trap from switch "$4" port "$5"

FastPattern.description: 36, UserLogoff: SW_Management:Kicked OOB user
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(SW_Management):\s*Kicked OOB user '([^']+)' with mac ([A-F\d:]{17}) on port (\d+) of switch ([.\d]+).*

FastPattern.description: 36, UserLogoff: SW_Management:Kicked OOB user (format 2)
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(SW_Management):\s*Kicked OOB user \[OOB ## ([A-F\d:]{17}) ## ([.\d]+)/([^]]+)\] (.+?) on port (\d+) of switch ([.\d]+).*

FastPattern.description: 37, ServiceWarning: SW_Management:There are multiple MAC address associated with switch
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(SW_Management):\s*There are multiple MAC (?:address|addresses) associated with switch \[([.\d]+)\] port \[([^]]+)\]\.*
FastPattern.pattern: SW_Management:\s*There are multiple MAC (?:address|addresses) associated with switch

FastField.defaultValue: Multiple MAC address associated with switch "$4" port "$5"
Multiple MAC address associated with switch "$4" port "$5"

FastPattern.description: 45, ConfigurationTrafficAudit: SW_Management:Received WlcTrapEvent [type=LWAPP_DISASSOC]
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(SW_Management):\s*Received WlcTrapEvent \[type=(\S+) wlc_ip=([.\w:]+) mac=([A-Fa-f\d:]+) ip=([.\w:]+) ssid=(\S+) apmac=([A-Fa-f\d:]+)[^]]*\]\.\s*([^]]+) \[OOB ## ([^#]+) ## ([^]]+)\] (\S+)\.

FastPattern.description: 38, SoftwareUpdate: CleanAccess:Automatic update failed
39, UserAuthAudit: Administration:Invalid admin credentials
40, UserAuthAudit: Administration:AutoConnectManager successfully re-linked CAM with CAS
FastPattern.pattern: Administration:\s*AutoConnectManager successfully re-linked CAM with CAS

FastField.defaultValue: AutoConnectManager successfully re-linked CAM with CAS "$4"
Administration:AutoConnectManager successfully re-linked CAM with CAS-$4

FastPattern.description: 41, UserLogoff: Authentication: Logout attempt failed
42, SystemStatus: CleanAccessServer: System Stats
43, ServiceWarning: CleanAccessServer: IP disconnected
44, SystemStatus: CleanAccessServer: HA status alert of Clean Access Server
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(CleanAccessServer):\s*HA status alert of Clean Access Server \[([.\d]+)\] : (.*)
FastPattern.pattern: CleanAccessServer:\s*HA status alert of Clean Access Server

FastField.defaultValue: HA status alert of Clean Access Server "$4"
HA status alert of Clean Access Server "$4"

FastPattern.description: 45, ServiceInfo: Administration: license is valid
46, UserLogoff: Administration: Admin user logged out
FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) (\S+).*(Administration):\s*Admin user logged out\. Name:([^,]+), Group:([^,]+), IP:([^,]+), .+.*

FastPattern.description: 47, ServiceWarning: SW_Management:SNMP trap is received from switch NOT in our database
FastPattern.pattern: SW_Management:\s*[\w]+ trap is received from switch \[[\w.]+\] which is NOT in our database\.

FastPattern.description: NullAlert: Authentication: Kick users based on MAC list provided by the Clean Access
FastPattern.pattern: Authentication:\s*Kick users based on MAC list provided by the Clean Access

FastPattern.description: NullAlert: snort messges
